  "name": "Blood Curse of Dull Reality",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/light/light-candles-lit-white.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a bonus action, you dull the sense a creature within 30 feet of you, making them unreliable. Until the end of your next turn, the cursed creature has disadvantage on all Wisdom (Perception) checks and does not benefit from features such as Keen Hearing, Devil's Sight, Tremor Sense or similar features.<br /><br /><strong>Amplify</strong>. This curse lasts up to 1 minute. Starting after the end of your next turn, the cursed creature can make a Charisma saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the curse on itself on a success.</p>",
